    "message": "When Ron Kirk (centre) arrived in Darwin in the 1970s, he planned to stay for just six months! 🤔\n\nMore than 51 years later, Ron is hanging up the headset alongside Mark Mahood (left) and Andrew Clark (right). All three were in our System Control team and together they've clocked up more than 131 years helping to keep the lights on across the Territory. 💡\n\nThey've seen - and adapted to - plenty of change over that time, embracing new technology and sharing their knowledge with the next generation.\n\nThank you, Ron, Andrew and Mark. We wish you all the very best for a well-earned retirement! 👏\n\n#SystemControl #Retirement #SharingKnowledge",
